.....I can be brown I can be blue I can be violet sky..... clearly sierra isn't a soil expert.  

after the reading the definition, it seems like this term is very very specific and I have a hard time thinking about how a researcher trying to catalog their sample at NMDC will experimentally analyze it to the composition levels in this definition unless the composition of the soil is the purpose of the experiment.  Comparing this definition to plinthosol for example -- I can imagine someone picking plinthosol even if soil compsition isn't the main focus of the experiment because it talks more generally about soil composition ... could be a critical set of parameters/distinctions for real soil scientists however.  So I don't know about red soil; defer to experts.
